principles:
  - functional, no classes
  - test first, code later (TDD)
  - CLEAN is overkill and overuses layering (lasagna code)

layers:
  - database: functions that do database queires only
  - validators: functions tha throw errors based on their parameters
  - functions: functions that do any other nice stuff for us
  - controllers: just like other functions, but they receive req and res objects, and could either shortcut requests or call next()

-- Use cases --

sign up
  - validate form
  - create user (insert on database)
  - send verification mail

create post
  - clean form
  - create post (insert on database)

create comment
  - clean form
  - create comment (insert on database)
  - send notification

edit post
  - clean form
  - edit post (update database)

edit comment
  - clean form
  - edit comment (update database)

react to post
  - insert on database
  - create/update notification

follow
  - follow user (update database)
  - create notification

unfollow
  - unfollow user (update database)